Core Competencies and Technical Skills
1.
Biochemistry & Enzymology: Standardization and optimization of protein isolation, over-expression, purification, and characterization (western blotting). Biochemical characterization using enzyme activity assays and abiotic stress assays.
2.
Antioxidant Assays: Hands-on assessment of stress treatments and biochemical analyses, including SOD, CAT, and APx.
3.
Molecular Biology: DNA/RNA extraction, plasmid isolation, PCR, and expression analysis utilizing qRT-PCR techniques. Transcriptome data analysis and primer designing.
4.
Plant-Microbe Interactions: Bacterial isolation of PGPRs, bioformulation, and identification using 16S rRNA sequencing. Chemotaxis assays and plant-microbe interaction studies.
5.
Data Analysis & Statistics: Bioinformatics, genome mining, in silico analysis, molecular docking, and dynamic simulation (GROMACS, Schrödinger). Proficiency in R and Python 3.0 for analytical data interpretation.
6.
Experimental Design: Strong background in problem-solving, troubleshooting, and scientific report writing.
