Plant Biochemist and Biotechnologist with over five years of experience in molecular biology, biochemistry, and bioinformatics. Skilled in designing, executing, and troubleshooting complex experiments related to biochemical assay development and plant-microbe interactions, apart from protein isolation, purification, and enzyme kinetic assays. Deep expertise in the genus Oryza (rice), focusing on genome-wide identification, molecular evolution, and metabolic pathways related to stress tolerance. Trained expertise in bioinformatics and genome mining to identify and characterise plant proteins and enzymes, essential for mapping India’s plant-based research landscape. Currently, awaiting PhD defense
